HEADWORD: Floriation
<hw>Flo`ri*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Ornamentation by means of flower forms, whether closely imitated or
conventionalized.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any floral ornament or decoration.</def>
<rj><au>Rock.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Floricomous</ent>⟦br⟧
